The answer is that the value 10 in the dataNS.dataNotSync data member in the original code in class RunSync will definitely be visible by any other thread that synchronizes on the rs object, and obtains the lock of rs AFTER the main thread has exited from the rs.run() method. The dataNS.setDataNotSync(10); call is made within a synchronized block (on the object rs), therefore by the JMM, any writes made to any variables made by the main thread right before the release of the rs lock, will be made visible (have happened-before) to any threads subsequently obtaining the lock on rs and then reading those variables.

Notice that any threads that were just sleeping while the main thread made the changes, and then try to read the value of dataNS WITHOUT obtaining the lock on rs, are NOT guaranteed to see the value 10, since there is no happens-before relation established between them reading dataNS and the main thread writing dataNS.

As an example, in the following completed main() method, the thread t1 is guaranteed to print 10, but this is because we start thread t1 AFTER the rs.run() code has executed; if we replaced the order of rs.run(); and t1.start(); the value 10 would be printed only if t1 got the lock AFTER rs.run() got the lock (and finished):

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        RunSync rs = new RunSync();
        Thread t1 = new Thread() {
            public void run() {
                synchronized(rs) {
                    System.out.println(rs.dataNS.getDataNotSync());  
                }  
            }
        };
        rs.run();
        t1.start();
    }
    
If in the code above we write &quot;t1.start();&quot; and then follow by &quot;rs.run()&quot;, in order for t1 to guarantee to print 10, we would need to write a &quot;while(cond) rs.wait()&quot; statement in the run() of our thread that would guarantee that we don&#39;t read the dataNS value before rs.run() has finished executing from the main thread, and we would need to call rs.notify() as the last statement of rs.run() method.

